Plants producing essential oils represent a large part of natural ﬂora and an important resource
in various ﬁelds such as the pharmaceutical, food, and cosmetic industries, thanks to their ﬂavour,
]. Essential oils are a complex mixture of hydrocarbons and
oxygenated hydrocarbons arising fromthe isoprenoid pathways and secreted by glandular trichomes
disseminated mainly onto the surface of plant organs; therefore, they have a pivotal role in the growth

]. Furthermore, they seemto mediate the plant relationship with abiotic
